{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017SCbEeNsPDbLYdRGa7sHv3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NxVepoEA2jTFApkjYKKU4x","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'EOF'\n# Ray Cluster Migration Plan\n**Namespace:** ray  \n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Status:** DRAFT – for review only. No changes have been applied.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State\n\n| Resource | Field | Current Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| ray-head Deployment | image | `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` |\n| ray-head Deployment | resources | `{}` (no requests/limits) |\n| ray-worker Deployment | image | `rayproject/ray:2.9.0` |\n| ray-worker Deployment | replicas | `1` |\n| ray-worker Deployment | resources | `{}` (no requests/limits) |\n| ray-head Service | type | `ClusterIP` |\n| ray-head Service | ports | `6379/TCP (gcs)` only |\n| ray-head Service | dashboard | not exposed |\n\n### Observed via kubectl\n\n```\n# Worker replica count\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-worker -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}'\n# → 1\n\n# Images\nkubectl -n ray get deploy ray-head ray-worker \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\"=\"}{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n# → ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n# → ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n\n# Resources (both deployments)\n# → resources: {}   (none set on either deployment)\n\n# ray-head Service ports\n# → 6379/TCP (gcs) — ClusterIP only, no dashboard port\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Proposed Changes for Next Upgrade Window\n\n### 2.1 Ray Version Upgrade: 2.9.0 → 2.10.0\n\nUpgrade both head and worker to the next stable minor release to pick up\nbug-fixes and performance improvements shipped in 2.10.x.\n\n### 2.2 Worker Scale-Out: 1 → 3 Replicas\n\nIncrease the worker pool from 1 to 3 replicas to provide parallelism for\ndistributed tasks and tolerate a single-worker failure without cluster stall.\n\n### 2.3 Resource Requests and Limits\n\nSet explicit CPU/memory requests and limits on both Deployments so the\nKubernetes scheduler can bin-pack correctly and the Vertical Pod Autoscaler\n(if enabled) has a baseline to work from.\n\nProposed values (adjust to cluster capacity):\n\n| Container | CPU request | CPU limit | Memory request | Memory limit |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| ray-head | 500m | 2000m | 1Gi | 4Gi |\n| ray-worker | 500m | 2000m | 1Gi | 4Gi |\n\n### 2.4 Expose Ray Dashboard on ray-head Service\n\nAdd port 8265 (Ray Dashboard HTTP) to the ray-head Service so operators can\nreach the dashboard for cluster monitoring without port-forwarding.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exact kubectl Commands (DO NOT RUN – review only)\n\n> These commands are listed for operator review. They must not be executed\n> until this plan has been approved and a maintenance window is scheduled.\n\n### Step 1 – Upgrade ray-head image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-head \\\n  ray-head=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n```\n\n### Step 2 – Upgrade ray-worker image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set image deployment/ray-worker \\\n  ray-worker=rayproject/ray:2.10.0\n```\n\n### Step 3 – Scale ray-worker to 3 replicas\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray scale deployment/ray-worker --replicas=3\n```\n\n### Step 4 – Set resource requests/limits on ray-head\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set resources deployment/ray-head \\\n  --requests=cpu=500m,memory=1Gi \\\n  --limits=cpu=2000m,memory=4Gi\n```\n\n### Step 5 – Set resource requests/limits on ray-worker\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray set resources deployment/ray-worker \\\n  --requests=cpu=500m,memory=1Gi \\\n  --limits=cpu=2000m,memory=4Gi\n```\n\n### Step 6 – Expose dashboard port on ray-head Service\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray patch service ray-head --type='json' -p='[\n  {\n    \"op\": \"add\",\n    \"path\": \"/spec/ports/-\",\n    \"value\": {\n      \"name\": \"dashboard\",\n      \"port\": 8265,\n      \"protocol\": \"TCP\",\n      \"targetPort\": 8265\n    }\n  }\n]'\n```\n\n### Step 7 – Verify rollout\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-head\nkubectl -n ray rollout status deployment/ray-worker\nkubectl -n ray get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ray\nkubectl -n ray get svc ray-head\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Rollback Plan\n\nIf either Deployment rollout fails or the cluster becomes unhealthy:\n\n```bash\n# Rollback ray-head to previous revision\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-head\n\n# Rollback ray-worker to previous revision\nkubectl -n ray rollout undo deployment/ray-worker\n\n# Verify pod health after rollback\nkubectl -n ray get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ray\n```\n\nTo remove the dashboard port added to the Service, patch it back:\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n ray patch service ray-head --type='json' -p='[\n  {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/spec/ports/1\"}\n]'\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Approval Checklist\n\n- [ ] Plan reviewed by cluster owner\n- [ ] Maintenance window scheduled\n- [ ] Backup of current Deployment manifests taken (`kubectl -n ray get deploy -o yaml > ray-deploy-backup.yaml`)\n- [ ] Monitoring alerts silenced for maintenance window\n- [ ] Rollback procedure rehearsed\nEOF\necho \"Plan written: $(wc -l < /tmp/plan.md) lines\"","description":"Write migration plan to temp file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":745,"cache_read_input_tokens":29932,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":745},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd4552cf-ca58-4b11-8252-08b65d44d1a1","uuid":"7ae218e3-eb70-4808-8a4b-ba54da659b04","request_id":"req_011Cc2hNqm7NZedgMf6o6rNc"}
